properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued January 17 at 3:56PM EST until January 19 at 1:00PM EST by NWS Marquette MI
properties.description:
* WHAT...Heavy snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 12 to 16
inches. Winds gusting as high as 35 mph Saturday morning.

* WHERE...Keweenaw and Northern Houghton Counties.

* WHEN...From 10 PM this evening to 1 PM EST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...This will be a long duration winter storm.
The heaviest snow with snowfall rates of up to one inch per hour
is expected Saturday morning. Lighter snow with snowfall rates
around half an inch per hour is expected to continue from
Saturday afternoon into Sunday morning.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 10 PM THIS EVENING TO 1 PM EST SUNDAY
